# Keep Docs In Sync

After completing any task that changes how the app works, update the relevant spec doc in `docs/` before finishing.

## What Triggers a Doc Update

| Change Made | Doc to Update |
|-------------|---------------|
| Schema change (new table, column, relationship) | `docs/02-database-schema.md` |
| New or changed API endpoint | `docs/03-api-design.md` |
| UI layout or interaction change | relevant `docs/04` through `docs/07` |
| New library, tool, or infra decision | `docs/01-tech-stack.md` |
| New feature idea surfaced during build | `docs/10-future-ideas.md` |

## What to Update

- **Resolved an open decision?** Remove the checkbox and write the decision inline as a fact.
- **Made a structural change?** Update tables, diagrams, or code blocks to match reality.
- **Deviated from the spec?** Note what changed and why under an `## As Built` section in that doc.
- **New open question surfaced?** Add it to the `## Open Decisions` section of the relevant doc.

## What Not to Do

- Do not leave `## Open Decisions` items checked off without recording the actual decision.
- Do not add a new library to the codebase without updating `docs/01-tech-stack.md`.
- Do not skip updates because the change feels small — small undocumented decisions compound into confusion.
